[SN]TITLE[SN]
Mark Howard: Bolton Wanderers sign ex-Sheffield United goalkeeper

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Bolton Wanderers have signed free-agent goalkeeper Mark Howard on a two-year deal following his departure from Sheffield United.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 29-year-old was allowed to leave Bramall Lane at the end of his contract, having played 16 games last season for the Blades.
After leaving Arsenal in 2006, Howard has been with six clubs including St Mirren, Aberdeen and Blackpool.
He joined Sheffield United under then boss Danny Wilson in July 2012.
